tor[0]; // 获取第一个元素 for (int i = 0; i < size - 1; i++) { vector[i] = vector[i + 1]; // 向前移动每个元素 } vector[size - 1] = first_element; // 将第一个元素放到最后一个位置 // 输出移动后的向量 for (int i = 0; i < size; i++) { std::cout << vector[i] << \\" \\"; } return 0; } \`\`\` 在这个例子中，首先使用一个整数数组\`vector\`来表示向量，并计算向量的大小。然后，我们使用循环将每个元素向前移动一个位置，将第一个元素覆盖掉它前面的元素。最后，将保存的第一个元素放到向量的最后一个位置。最后，输出移动后的向量。 如果你将以上代码编译并运行，你将获得输出结果\`2 3 4 5 1\`。"},{"instruction":"As a prompt generator for a generative AI called \\"Midjourney\\", you will create image prompts for the AI to visualize. I will give you a concept, and you will provide a detailed prompt for Midjourney AI to generate an image. Please adhere to the structure and formatting below, and follow these guidelines: Do not use the words \\"description\\" or \\":\\" in any form. Do not place a comma between [ar] and [v]. Write each prompt in one line without using return. Structure: [1] = Front view,a chinese handsomeyoung man long hair man wearing hanfu, GoPro, in the style of ethereal portraiture. byPolina Washington, chinese style, playing theight and shadow, bauhaus photography, fuji28mm, hypercolorful dreamscapes, camilleclaudel, selective focus, Soft illumination/ soft lights --ar 3:4 --niji 5 --s 750 [2] = a detailed description of [1] with specific imagery details. [3] = a detailed description of the scene's environment. [4] = a detailed description of the compositions. [5] = a detailed description of the scene's mood, feelings, and atmosphere. [6] = A style (e.g. photography, painting, illustration, sculpture, artwork, paperwork, 3D, etc.) for [1]. [7] = a detailed description of the scene's mood, feelings, and atmosphere. [ar] = Use \\"--ar 16:9\\" for horizontal images, \\"--ar 9:16\\" for vertical images, or \\"--ar 1:1\\" for square images. [v] = Use \\"--niji\\" for Japanese art style, or \\"--v 5\\" for other styles. Formatting: Follow this prompt structure: \\"/imagine prompt: [1], [2], [3], [4], [5], [6], [7], [ar] [v]\\". Your task: Create 4 